	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>&nbsp;<u><i><font color="#FFFF00">BASIC CONTROLS:</font></i></u><br>
                  &nbsp; Move cursor:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;D-Pad or Left or Right Analog Stick</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Cancel command and return to previous menu:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Circle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Execute commands / Scroll messages and dialog displayed in windows:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;X Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Choose weapons during battle:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Square Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Displays the accuracy of enemy's counterattack when ally unit's attack accuracy is displayed during battle / Opens the parts data screen while in setup screen / Opens the menu window while on the network screen:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Triangle Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Rotate perspective during battle / Scroll through lists on the setup screen / Change class defense during battle setup:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L1 or R1 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Select allay unit that has not taken action during players phase / Changes target when selecting an enemy unit if multiple enemies are in attack range / Changes the character selected in setup and upgrade:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;L2 or R2 Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Confirm the location of units hidden behind obsticales on the strategic map:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Select Button</font>
                  <br>&nbsp; Open the system window during battle / Skip dialogues, messages, events and CG movies:
                  <font color="#00FF00">&nbsp;Start Button</font><br><br>
        &nbsp;</td>
	 </tr>
	</table>
